column5: Thought a muskie might come our way on this warm evening. Trolled and cast on the east side of the lake for 3 hrs without a sniff or follow.  Captpierre

I got a 33 incher on tuesday, then later in the day i was reeling in a half pound smallmouth and a huge muskie grabbed it, took plenty of drag, but couldn't get it off bottom, it eventually let go and i never saw it. But, it was BIG!
I'm hittin' the BOG on Saturday... Hoping to lay into some good slabs!
